race.comment: MISS KIM KAR (11) has been warming into her races late after being forced back from awkward draws, and she finally gets the chance to take closer order. Already a track-and-trip winner, bold showing anticipated. DUVANA (5) has settled in beautifully for Nathan Doyle and finds a very suitable assignment to keep the momentum going. Llewellyn sticks with the 3kg claim and is drawn ideally. Can give this a serious shake. SOVEREIGN HILL (4) is breathing fire chasing the hat-trick and will give another bold sight in front. If they hand him cheap sectionals, he'll take catching again. PICTOR (16) resumes and looks to have come back in terrific order, trialling strongly around some sharp types. The draw is a horror, but with even luck he can be right in the finish. INTERJECTION (6) will likely get a long way back but can produce a late scare if they overcook it up front. OFF THE PRESS (10) made encouraging late ground last start and is one to include in the minors.
